Implemented `oauth-client-credentials-grant` and wrote the handoff to [state/last-result.txt](/Users/stevenna/WebstormProjects/mina-mock-mcpserver/state/last-result.txt).

What changed: `/oauth/token` now dispatches both `authorization_code` and `client_credentials`; client credentials validate enabled client ID/secret, issue `sub=client:<client_id>` JWTs with `grant_type=client_credentials`, use the client credentials TTL, and compute endpoint permissions from all allowed endpoints or the requested scope intersection. Issued token storage now supports machine tokens with nullable `oauthUserId`.

Added coverage in [tests/unit/oauth-token.test.ts](/Users/stevenna/WebstormProjects/mina-mock-mcpserver/tests/unit/oauth-token.test.ts) and [tests/e2e/oauth-client-credentials.spec.ts](/Users/stevenna/WebstormProjects/mina-mock-mcpserver/tests/e2e/oauth-client-credentials.spec.ts), plus the Prisma migration and scoped docs/progress updates.

